New Records: Caden Dana became the youngest Angels pitcher since Francisco Rodríguez in 2002 -- and the club’s youngest starting pitcher since Frank Tanana in 1973.
Key Match Events: Dana allowed two runs on two hits, four strikeouts and four walks through the first six innings.
Pre-Game Insights: Dana said he was nervous but knew his nerves would release after the first pitch.
Dana's close circle, including his parents and high school coaches, were present at the game.
Post-Match Reflections: Amanda Dana reflected on her son's hard work and said she was proud of him.
Fred Dana, Caden's father, was visibly emotional and proud of his son's performance.
Coaches Mike Rooney, Jim Wladkya, and Mike Dwyer expressed immense pride in Caden's debut.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Dana retired the side on 12 pitches in the first inning.
Dana recorded his first career strikeout against Cal Raleigh.
Dana limited Seattle to just a Luke Raley solo homer in the second and Victor Robles’ sacrifice fly in the third.
